Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Halve, peel and
thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g} and
@Portobello mushrooms{2}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a
#garlic press{}). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped,
stalks and all). Pour half the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} into a #bowl{}, add the
@olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with salt and pepper. Mix together and leave to the
side. This is your dressing.

Add the @penne pasta{180%g} to the boiling water, simmer until tender,
~{12%minutes}. When the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back into the
pan, drizzle with a little oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.
Set aside off the heat.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat.
Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and stir-fry for ~{2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Add the mushrooms and cook until browned, stirring occasionally, ~{6-7%minutes}.
Once browned, reduce the heat to medium-low and add the onion. Cook, stirring
frequently until the onion is nice and soft, ~{5-6%minutes}, then add the garlic,
season with salt and pepper. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the remaining
balsamic vinegar, stir and cook until evaporated, ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook lardons thoroughly

Pour the @water{150%ml} into your frying pan and stir in the
@vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Increase the heat and bring to the boil, then
reduce the heat to low and simmer until reduced, ~{5-6%minutes}, stir occasionally.
Stir in the @creme fraiche{99%g} until well combined, bring back to the boil and
add a good grind of black pepper. Remove from the heat.

Add the drained pasta to the sauce along with three quarters of the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and three quarters of the parsley. Stir
everything together. Taste and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Spoon your pasta into bowls and sprinkle the remaining cheese and parsley on
top. Add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the balsamic dressing and toss together.
Serve on top of the pasta, finish with a good grind of black pepper and enjoy!

> MOD: If you've opted to get bacon added to your meal, add the lardons to your pan
> before you add the mushrooms and cook for 2 mins. Then add the mushrooms and
> continue with the rest of the recipe as instructed.